        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 5:01PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Montrose, or near Flushing, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flint, Flushing, Davison, Clio, Burton, Mount Morris, Montrose,
Otisville, Lennon, Otter Lake, Beecher, Crossroads Village, Genesee,
and Thetford Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
